<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36028c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36028c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36028c"> 28(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Archibald, Ninth, / Earl of <font color="green">[Alrgile]</font> <font color="green">[sic]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Of the castle &hellip; In the armoury is a collection of arms of various dates; and on the Argyll battery stands a huge piece of ancient artillery, called Mons Meg, of which repeated mention is made in Scottish history. Argyll Tower, in which <mark>Archibald, 9th earl of Argyll</mark>, spent his last days (1685), was also restored in 1892 by Mr. William Nelson. <small> &ldquo;EDINBURGH&rdquo; <a name="EBED" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBED"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 937b-c</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
